params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. Job name. For example: "projects/123456/locations/us-central1/jobs/job01".

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. A system generated unique ID (in UUID4 format) for the Job.

params.name: data.priority
params.description: Priority of the Job. The valid value range is [0, 100). A job with higher priority value is more likely to run earlier if all other requirements are satisfied.

params.name: data.task_groups
params.description: Required. TaskGroups in the Job. Only one TaskGroup is supported now.

params.name: data.allocation_policy
params.description: Compute resource allocation for all TaskGroups in the Job.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Labels for the Job. Labels could be user provided or system generated. For example, "labels": { "department": "finance", "environment": "test" } You can assign up to 64 labels. Google Compute Engine label restrictions apply. Label names that start with "goog-" or "google-" are reserved.

params.description: Output only. The last time the Job was updated.
